Good Technical Infosec Blogs?
text:
I'm looking for really good technical blogs or even blog posts. From stepping through gritty details of exploits to big picture ideas even to discussion about specific tools, how they work, and pros and cons. I am just finding myself, having been in field for five years or so, really hungry for more quality info.

There are tons of company marketing blogs that are largely superficial, but finding good technical or in-depth blogs is a bit harder. I've read some good stuff from Dark Reading and Bleeping Computer. The SANS blogs can be good as well. That about covers what I largely have followed. Hope some folks have some interesting reads to share.

edit: podcasts and other media forms are great as well

title: Show HN: Command line utility for working with HuggingFace diffuser pipelines
text: i created this to scratch an itch. used to generate images with any diffusion pipeline which is compatible with the huggingface diffuser library. dead simple command line interface, offline-first workflow, and features a simple TOML config for reusing common prompts or flags.

Spotify didn't release wrapped this year for some countries for no reason
text:
Spotify wrapped, the story like thing that shows you the stats of what you've been listening to every year like what artists/songs/genres you've been listening to the whole year just dropped.

but the thing that's not talked about anywhere is that Spotify wrapped didn't release in some countries/regions where it was released previous years such as Rwanda, Venezuela, Bangladesh etc.

This is a bfd because Spotify wrapped is insightful and actually useful and them just removing the feature overnight for premium users without even notifying them is weird. the Spotify community site is filled with these complaints but staff won't reply or say anything about it, completely ignoring it. I kinda wished some media sites atleast reported it and then Spotify would say why they didn't release wrapped for some countries (mostly developing countries).

And it's not the first time either. many Spotify features are unavailable in my own region without explanation even though I'm a premium user. The list includes: Spotify canvas, video podcast, audiobooks, hey Spotify, karaoke mode, the Storyline feature and more... We are just treated unequally and it sucks.
